26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_engine_disp_sorgm204.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:31 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "nv50.h"
30#include "outpdp.h"
31
32#include <subdev/timer.h>
33
34static inline u32
35gm204_sor_soff(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp)
36{
37 return (ffs(outp->base.info.or) - 1) * 0x800;
38}
39
40static inline u32
41gm204_sor_loff(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp)
42{
43 return gm204_sor_soff(outp) + !(outp->base.info.sorconf.link & 1) * 0x80;
44}
45
46void
47gm204_sor_magic(struct nvkm_output *outp)
48{
49 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->disp->engine.subdev.device;
50 const u32 soff = outp->or * 0x100;
51 const u32 data = outp->or + 1;
52 if (outp->info.sorconf.link & 1)
53 nvkm_mask(device, 0x612308 + soff, 0x0000001f, 0x00000000 | data);
54 if (outp->info.sorconf.link & 2)
55 nvkm_mask(device, 0x612388 + soff, 0x0000001f, 0x00000010 | data);
56}
57
58static inline u32
59gm204_sor_dp_lane_map(struct nvkm_device *device, u8 lane)
60{
61 return lane * 0x08;
62}
63
64static int
65gm204_sor_dp_pattern(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp, int pattern)
66{
67 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->base.disp->engine.subdev.device;
68 const u32 soff = gm204_sor_soff(outp);
69 const u32 data = 0x01010101 * pattern;
70 if (outp->base.info.sorconf.link & 1)
71 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61c110 + soff, 0x0f0f0f0f, data);
72 else
73 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61c12c + soff, 0x0f0f0f0f, data);
74 return 0;
75}
76
77static int
78gm204_sor_dp_lnk_pwr(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp, int nr)
79{
80 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->base.disp->engine.subdev.device;
81 const u32 soff = gm204_sor_soff(outp);
82 const u32 loff = gm204_sor_loff(outp);
83 u32 mask = 0, i;
84
85 for (i = 0; i < nr; i++)
86 mask |= 1 << (gm204_sor_dp_lane_map(device, i) >> 3);
87
88 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61c130 + loff, 0x0000000f, mask);
89 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61c034 + soff, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
90 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
91 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c034 + soff) & 0x80000000))
92 break;
93 );
94 return 0;
95}
96
97static int
98gm204_sor_dp_drv_ctl(struct nvkm_output_dp *outp,
99 int ln, int vs, int pe, int pc)
100{
101 struct nvkm_device *device = outp->base.disp->engine.subdev.device;
102 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
103 const u32 shift = gm204_sor_dp_lane_map(device, ln);
104 const u32 loff = gm204_sor_loff(outp);
105 u32 addr, data[4];
106 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
107 struct nvbios_dpout info;
108 struct nvbios_dpcfg ocfg;
109
110 addr = nvbios_dpout_match(bios, outp->base.info.hasht,
111 outp->base.info.hashm,
112 &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &info);
113 if (!addr)
114 return -ENODEV;
115
116 addr = nvbios_dpcfg_match(bios, addr, pc, vs, pe,
117 &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &ocfg);
118 if (!addr)
119 return -EINVAL;
120 ocfg.tx_pu &= 0x0f;
121
122 data[0] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c118 + loff) & ~(0x000000ff << shift);
123 data[1] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c120 + loff) & ~(0x000000ff << shift);
124 data[2] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c130 + loff);
125 if ((data[2] & 0x00000f00) < (ocfg.tx_pu << 8) || ln == 0)
126 data[2] = (data[2] & ~0x00000f00) | (ocfg.tx_pu << 8);
127 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c118 + loff, data[0] | (ocfg.dc << shift));
128 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c120 + loff, data[1] | (ocfg.pe << shift));
129 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c130 + loff, data[2]);
130 data[3] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c13c + loff) & ~(0x000000ff << shift);
131 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61c13c + loff, data[3] | (ocfg.pc << shift));
132 return 0;
133}
134
135static const struct nvkm_output_dp_func
136gm204_sor_dp_func = {
137 .pattern = gm204_sor_dp_pattern,
138 .lnk_pwr = gm204_sor_dp_lnk_pwr,
139 .lnk_ctl = gf119_sor_dp_lnk_ctl,
140 .drv_ctl = gm204_sor_dp_drv_ctl,
141};
142
143int
144gm204_sor_dp_new(struct nvkm_disp *disp, int index, struct dcb_output *dcbE,
145 struct nvkm_output **poutp)
146{
147 return nvkm_output_dp_new_(&gm204_sor_dp_func, disp, index, dcbE, poutp);
148}
